main event: A civilian man observed a white, arc-shaped object flashing on and off for about 20 to 30 minutes in Redwing, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The object appeared to disappear instantly., The nature of the blinking and the duration of the observation were noted to be characteristic of a star., Only one object was reported during the observation., The incident occurred during overcast conditions., The report is part of the Project Blue Book records from the U.S. Air Force.
